condition.narrative: Section 1.A.2.(e) of Schedule 2 of Loan Agreement: No later than ninety (90) days after the Effective Date and without limitationto the provisions of paragraph 2(a) of this Section, the Borrower shall hire two accountants for Project implementation.

Section 1.B.1.(a) of Schedule 2 of Loan Agreement: No later than four months after the Effective Date, the Borrower shall acquireand install computerized accounting software for Project implementation, acceptable to the Bank.

Section 1.B.1.(b) of Schedule 2 of Loan Agreement: No later than six months after the Effective Date, the Borrower shall contractthe services of an external auditor for the Project, under terms of reference and with qualifications and experience acceptable tothe Bank.

Section 1.B.2 of Schedule 2 of Loan Agreement: For purposes of carrying out the Project, the Borrower, through MINEA, shall withinthirty (30) days after the Effective Date enter into a memorandum of understanding (MoU) with each of RNT, ENDE and PRODEL, underterms and conditions acceptable to the Bank, which shall include, inter alia: (i) the respective roles and responsibilities ofMINEA, RNT, ENDE and PRODEL in the implementation of the Project, including the appointment of counterpart teams at each of RNT,ENDE and PRODEL; and (ii) the requirements to befollowed for the implementation on the part of each agency, including withoutlimitation the obligation of RNT, ENDE and PRODEL to comply with the provisions of this Agreement and the ESCP.

Section 1.B.3.(a) of Schedule 2 of Loan Agreement: The Borrower shall cause each of PRODEL, RNT and ENDE, within thirty (30) daysafter the Effective Date, to designate and maintain throughout Project implementation, counterpart teams within each technicalagency. Each counterpart team shall have at least a focal point and be composed of such other persons covering the key projectimplementation functions (technical/engineering, procurement, financial management and environmental and social risks management)as further detailed in the POM.
